      "raw_text": "After a consultation yesterday\nwith the members Of the board OF\npublic works and the city engineer\nMayor Daggett called special\nmeeting of the city council for\nThursday night to discuss and take\nsome immediate action upon the\nbridge question. The meeting is\npostponed on account Of Council\nman Pratt's absence.\n\n\nThe board OF public works had\noffers from both the Traction CON-\npany and the Washington Water\nPower company to stand Aalf the\nexpenses Of putting in new bridges\non streets used by their carllnes.\n\n\nSecretary Blocker, speaking for\nthe officials of the Washington\nWater Power company, has already\nagreed to stand all the expense OF\nthe reconstruction of the Howard\nstreet bridge in place of the one\nthat collapsed, but the special ses-\nsion of the council has been called"
